    ('Plain Dosa', 'rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves', 25, 200, 'easy', 'veg', 'healthy', 'south-indian', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the Plain Dosa with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar'),
