    ('Modak', 'rice flour and coconut, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves', 30, 340, 'medium', 'veg', 'healthy', 'sweets', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the rice flour and coconut with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar'),
    ('Puran Poli', 'lentil and jaggery, whole wheat flour, salt, oil, ghee, water', 40, 280, 'medium', 'veg', 'comfort', 'sweets', 'Knead a soft dough with 2 cups flour, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 tsp oil and about 3/4 cup water; cover and rest 20 minutes; Divide into 6 balls; roll out, stuffing with lentil and jaggery if required, and dust with dry flour; Cook on a hot tawa 1-2 minutes per side, brushing with ghee, until golden brown spots appear and it puffs; Serve warm with curd, pickle or curry'),
